led to post human-intervention comment to issue #{issue_number}: {exc!r}\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3381:    \"\"\"Post a human-intervention comment and label when an issue run needs follow-up.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:3399:            f\"ERROR: Failed to apply human-intervention follow-up to issue #{claimed_issue.issue['number']}: {exc!r}\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:5675:            \"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \"\nforge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:325:    generated_loc = count_generated_loc(tests_root)\nforge/utility_scripts/gradle_test_runner.py:140:The command was stopped as a suspected test deadlock or leaked-thread hang. Fix the generated tests so every test\nforge/utility_scripts/local_ci_verification.py:25:HUMAN_INTERVENTION_LABEL = \"human-intervention\"\nforge/utility_scripts/source_context.py:178:        \"discoverArtifactMetadata\",\nforge/utility_scripts/source_context.py:195:            f\"ERROR: discoverArtifactMetadata failed for {coordinate}. See {log_path_display} for details.\",\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:89:- Iteratively generate a meaningful, cohesive JUnit test suite for library using AI.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:123:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:418:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\nforge/benchmarks/benchmark_runner.py:70:            \"Forwarded to add_new_library_support.py. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access strategies \"\nforge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:351:            forge_metadata.gh(\"issue\", \"edit\", \"2099\", \"--add-label\", \"human-intervention\")\nforge/tests/test_make_pr_not_for_native_image.py:92:        self.assertIn(\"human-intervention\", create_call)\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:87:- the generated test suite is valid, cohesive, and meaningful for the target library\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:91:- nothing in the generated output suggests the agent solved the task by breaking or trivializing the test\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:115:Coverage and other metrics do not need a single universal threshold, but they must look credible for the library size and the generated test shape. Suspiciously low coverage, near-empty tests, or inflated metadata with weak tests should be treated as failures that need investigation.\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:123:- the generated test logic is valid and meaningful\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:137:- generated tests are trivial, broken, or misleading\nforge/docs/ai-workflow-testing.md:158:- describe the important observations from logs, generated tests, and metrics\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:68:7. Use the same finalization path to generate metadata, validate tests, collect stats, and commit.\nforge/docs/architecture.md:158:  posts a human-intervention comment. Also runs the PR review queues.\nforge/docs/architecture.md:171:| [improve_library_coverage.py](../ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py) | `library-update-request` | Resolve an existing-library update target, clone/split support when needed, then generate tests + metadata to improve coverage for the requested coordinate. |\nforge/docs/architecture.md:335:        Disp->>GH: Push preserve branch + human-intervention comment\nforge/tests/test_library_update_target.py:544:            generated_test = os.path.join(target.test_dir, \"src\", \"test\", \"java\", \"GeneratedTest.java\")\nforge/tests/test_library_update_target.py:547:            _write_file(generated_test, \"class GeneratedTest {}\\n\")\nforge/tests/test_library_update_target.py:553:                    os.remove(generated_test)\nforge/tests/test_library_update_target.py:566:            self.assertTrue(os.path.isfile(generated_test))\nforge/ai_workflows/java_fail_workflow.py:293:    \"\"\"Commit the generated candidate that already passed the workflow test loop.\"\"\"\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:53:| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:198:shared repository file changed, the PR must be labeled `human-intervention`\nforge/tests/test_git_worktree_regressions.py:241:                    return_value=\"ai/test/human-intervention/issue-1412\",\nforge/docs/native-metadata-exploration.md:286:Sequencing with `generateMetadata`, native-test verification, codex fixup,\nforge/tests/test_native_test_verification.py:348:        The gate runs generateMetadata and test before any trace fallback.\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:9:  - `run(...)`: runs a single generation attempt. It generates the initial dynamic-access report, falls back to `BasicIterativeStrategy` only if no usable guidance exists at the start, otherwise enters the dynamic-access class iteration immediately and counts success only after metadata generation, retest, `generateLibraryStats`, and a commit for the library iteration succeed.\nforge/tests/test_make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:61:        self.assertIn(\"human-intervention\", labels)\nforge/docs/native-test-verification.md:82:  Gradle log (`generateMetadata`, `test`, or `runNativeTraceImage`).\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:261:    Keep -- yes --> KeepOK([Phase returns ok=true,<br/>keep generated tests])\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:283:    GenMD[generateMetadata] --> Test{./gradlew test passes?}\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:324:| Reachability-repo Gradle tasks | `scaffold`, `populateArtifactURLs`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `test`, `nativeTest`, `generateMetadata`, `generateLibraryStats`. |\nforge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py:53:            \"   or an unsupported platform feature), remove the generated test that causes that failure.\",\nforge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py:54:            \"   You may also remove generated test-only files that are only needed by that failing test.\",\nforge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py:45:    (e.g. scaffold a library, generate metadata, run tests, iterate on fixes).\nforge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:82:            \"Iteratively generate and validate unit tests for a given library using the configured agent.\\n\\n\"\nforge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py:145:            \"When using dynamic-access strategies, keep generated tests even when they do not improve \"\nforge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:251:                    self._print_dynamic_access_message(\"Coverage not improved. Keeping generated tests by request.\")\nforge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:787:        \"\"\"Capture tracked and untracked changes under the generated library test tree.\"\"\"\nforge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/basic_iterative_strategy.py:17:    │   https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/docs/CONTRIBUTING.md#generate-metadata-and-test   │\nforge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/basic_iterative_strategy.py:203:                        f\"Checkpoint generated tests for {self.library} ({unittest_number})\"\nforge/prompt_templates/initial/basic_initial.md:4:You need to generate comprehensive tests for the library defined by these Maven coordinates: {library}.\nforge/prompt_templates/initial/basic_initial.md:22:- When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally requires open-ended dynamic class loading that Native Image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, catch `Error`, verify it with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`, and re-throw if it does not match. This proves Native Image fails for the right reason instead of skipping the test.\nforge/prompt_templates/persistent/dynamic_access_rules.md:4:- Maintain a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files.\nforge/prompt_templates/persistent/dynamic_access_rules.md:18:- Never generate, write, or modify reachability metadata or Native Image config entries. Do not create or edit `reachability-metadata.json`, `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, `predefined-classes-config.json`, or any other file under `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image`; Forge handles metadata generation and merging externally.\nforge/prompt_templates/persistent/dynamic_access_rules.md:19:- When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally requires open-ended dynamic class loading that Native Image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, catch `Error`, verify it with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`, and re-throw if it does not match. This proves Native Image fails for the right reason instead of skipping the test.\nforge/prompt_templates/persistent/default_agent_rules.md:4:- Keep generated tests meaningful and avoid replacing real coverage with trivial assertions.\nforge/prompt_templates/persistent/default_agent_rules.md:6:- Never generate, write, or modify reachability metadata or Native Image config entries. Do not create or edit `reachability-metadata.json`, `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, `predefined-classes-config.json`, or any other file under `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image`; Forge handles metadata generation and merging externally.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
